289
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:39,120
isn't it?

290
00:11:41,790 --> 00:11:42,200
What?

291
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:42,750
Hello?

292
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:44,630
Wh-what's fake?

293
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,270
Stop pretending!

294
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:47,200
I know you can hear me.

295
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:48,390
Listen up.

296
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,000
I won't go to our son's camping.

297
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:52,120
About our separation,

298
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,480
when are you telling him?

299
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,550
Let me tell you.

300
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:00,910
We absolutely can't tell him now.

301
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:01,910
Alright?

302
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,910
He's got midterms coming up.

303
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:04,670
Fine.

304
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,550
You won't tell him?

305
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:06,550
I will.

306
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:07,480
No!

307
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:09,320
If Daer finds out,

308
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,750
I swear I'll make you pay!

309
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:11,960
This isn't your decision.

310
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:12,720
Don't tell him!

311
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,600
Don't you dare, hear me?

312
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:18,510
I'm warning you.

313
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,270
If you dare say anything,

314
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:22,630
you'll never see the kid again!

315
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:23,480
How dare you!

316
00:12:24,030 --> 00:12:24,670
Just watch me!

317
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,120
I can't believe it!

318
00:12:27,510 --> 00:12:28,320
Calm down.

319
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,440
She actually threatened me.

320
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:41,390
Wait.

321
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,030
We haven't fixed
Ms. Zhou's affair yet.

322
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:43,440
Kiddo,

323
00:12:43,510 --> 00:12:45,320
I have some matters to attend to now.

324
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:47,150
Let's discuss that matter later, okay?

325
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:48,360
Wait.

326
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:49,630
Today's matter

327
00:12:49,630 --> 00:12:50,840
should be clarified today.

328
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:52,360
What exactly is wrong?

329
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:57,840
He has no other women outside

330
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,150
doesn't mean he's not a scammer.

331
00:13:01,510 --> 00:13:02,080
Think about it.

332
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:05,030
Ms. Zhou and her husband
were married nearly 40 years.

333
00:13:05,550 --> 00:13:06,550
He passed just two months ago,

334
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:07,360
and she has someone new.

335
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:08,630
She's buying him million-yuan annuities.

336
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:09,510
Is that normal?

337
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,080
Then how long would be normal?

338
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:11,900
Huh?

339
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:14,550
Ms. Zhou's husband passed away.

340
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:16,120
How soon should she move on?

341
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,080
What timeframe
would you consider normal?

342
00:13:19,270 --> 00:13:20,030
I can't say for sure.

343
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:21,440
But two months

344
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:22,960
is definitely too soon.

345
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,790
So, Ms. Zhou should be like you,

346
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,390
unable to move past the separation

347
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:28,270
and escape reality.

348
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:29,550
That would be normal, right?

349
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,480
Are you crazy?

350
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,200
Why bring me into this?

351
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,150
So what if you separated?

352
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:35,630
Why hiding it from the world?

353
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:36,200
Aren't you tired?

354
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,080
Isn't it escaping reality?

355
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:41,150
I'm not doing this for myself.

356
00:13:41,150 --> 00:13:42,480
I'm doing it for my son.

357
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:44,240
He'll be affected if he knows.

358
00:13:46,390 --> 00:13:47,320
Still fooling yourself.

359
00:13:49,630 --> 00:13:50,550
You know nothing!

360
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:52,320
I'm wasting my time,

361
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,840
standing here bickering with you.

362
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:08,870
Ms. Qiu and I have errands to run.

363
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,030
Go upstairs.

364
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,670
Call me if anything comes up.

365
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:13,200
Dad.

366
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:14,510
Get off.

367
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,630
We need to talk.

368
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:34,600
Yes?

369
00:14:35,870 --> 00:14:36,600
Did Mom upset you?

370
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:38,600
No.

371
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:39,870
Then did you upset Mom?

372
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:43,960
Daer.

373
00:14:44,870 --> 00:14:46,120
You're too young to understand.

374
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,030
When you're older...

375
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:48,320
Is it because of that woman in the car?

376
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:55,360
No.

377
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,750
I saw everything.

378
00:14:57,910 --> 00:14:58,600
She gave you

379
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:00,000
that car, didn't she?

380
00:15:02,550 --> 00:15:04,120
Give the car back to her.

381
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:06,200
Go home, and apologize to mom.

382
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:07,670
I'll put in a good word.

383
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:08,670
We can put this behind us.

384
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:10,320
You know how Mom is.

385
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:11,670
Tough on the outside,

386
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:12,910
but soft-hearted inside.

387
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,270
Your mom and I are separated.

388
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:19,750
What?

389
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,000
Your mom and I

390
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,550
split up a month ago.

391
00:16:28,510 --> 00:16:28,910
Dingding.

392
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:35,840
Dad took you to the therapist?

393
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,440
He kept saying he was busy

394
00:16:43,510 --> 00:16:44,480
and couldn't get away.

395
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:48,240
Said he was in the final push
of his retreat.

396
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,960
I saw how much you wanted him there,

397
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:51,910
so I thought...

398
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:52,670
You've separated?

399
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:03,750
He told you?

400
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:05,200
Why didn't you tell me?

401
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,480
Listen.

402
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:11,550
After all, this isn't a good thing.

403
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:12,240
Don't you agree?

404
00:17:14,830 --> 00:17:15,240
Dingding.

405
00:17:15,790 --> 00:17:16,110
Dingding.

406
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:17,640
Dingding.

407
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:19,240
What are you doing?

408
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:21,160
Open the door!

409
00:17:23,550 --> 00:17:24,030
Dingding.

410
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:27,590
Don't be angry, Dingding.

411
00:17:28,310 --> 00:17:30,030
You have exams coming up, remember?

412
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:31,920
I didn't want to affect your mood.

413
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,070
Your grandpa's blood pressure
is unstable too.

414
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,920
I was doing what's best for you, okay?

415
00:17:36,110 --> 00:17:36,510
Dingding.

416
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,240
Take it.

417
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,240
Throw it away, sell it, or whatever.

418
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:42,480
If you'd told me earlier,

419
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:44,270
I wouldn't have
accepted that woman's gift!

420
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,480
I wouldn't even have seen her.

421
00:17:58,590 --> 00:17:59,350
You're not mad at me?

422
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:02,400
Why would I?

423
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:14,440
I'm sorry.

424
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:17,350
I'm sorry.

425
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,640
You didn't do anything wrong.

426
00:18:20,510 --> 00:18:21,440
Why are you saying sorry?

427
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:25,880
It's all my fault.

428
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:31,070
Are you okay with us separating?

429
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:35,350
Separating?

430
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:38,000
Of course I don't want that.

431
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,270
But things have already come to this.

432
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:42,790
Mom...

433
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,000
Don't be sad.

434
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:45,590
You separated.

435
00:18:45,790 --> 00:18:46,160
No big deal.

436
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:47,920
No matter what,

437
00:18:48,790 --> 00:18:49,350
I'm here.

438
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:56,510
Come here.

439
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:00,070
I'm sorry.

440
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:02,070
I'm not a good mother.

441
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:05,790
I'm sorry.

442
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,200
Good. We've cleared it up.

443
00:19:31,350 --> 00:19:32,550
The child is tougher than

444
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:33,510
we imagined.

445
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:40,960
On another topic.

446
00:19:42,310 --> 00:19:44,920
Li Fendou has approached me
several times.

447
00:19:46,030 --> 00:19:46,510
Zhiyuan,

448
00:19:47,510 --> 00:19:48,030
how about

449
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:49,400
you set a time?

450
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:53,270
Another dinner meeting?

451
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:54,750
I think we should pass.

452
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:57,830
What are you afraid of?

453
00:19:58,550 --> 00:20:00,270
Li Fendou doesn't mind.

454
00:20:01,070 --> 00:20:01,750
Besides,

455
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:04,000
he's Zhig's landlord.

456
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:06,440
Just do this one favor for me, okay?

457
00:20:07,030 --> 00:20:08,590
It's not that I won't help you

458
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,640
I just lack confidence in myself.

459
00:20:11,830 --> 00:20:13,550
You know what kind of temper I have.

460
00:20:13,790 --> 00:20:16,680
If it's just casual dining and drinking

461
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:17,510
with light conversation,

462
00:20:17,790 --> 00:20:18,440
I'd be fine.

463
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:21,480
I'm just afraid those bosses
will play cultured

464
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,750
and start talking art and philosophy.

465
00:20:26,270 --> 00:20:28,270
When I hear those nonsensical opinions,

466
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,270
I can't help but argue back.

467
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:31,440
In the end,

468
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:33,790
instead of building rapport,

469
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,000
I'd just make things worse.

470
00:20:37,550 --> 00:20:38,030
Zhiyuan.

471
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,720
That's exactly where your charm lies.

472
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:42,070
Don't worry.

473
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:43,510
That Li Fendou

474
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:45,070
isn't some petty boss either.

475
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:46,350
Besides,

476
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:49,200
even if you did
say something to offend him,

477
00:20:49,510 --> 00:20:50,400
I wouldn't care at all.

478
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,720
Between you and him,

479
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:53,640
you're obviously more important.

480
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:57,030
If you're really unhappy,

481
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:58,400
just walk away.

482
00:20:58,880 --> 00:20:59,720
I won't stop you.

483
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,110
Alright?

484
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:05,160
Okay.

485
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:08,310
Thank you.

486
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:17,880
Haven't finished yet?

487
00:21:18,590 --> 00:21:19,720
Here, drink your milk.

488
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:25,240
Yes?

489
00:21:27,510 --> 00:21:30,000
You really don't blame me

490
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:31,680
for the separation?

491
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,480
Why would I blame you?

492
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:34,920
If anyone's to blame, it's Dad.

493
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:36,440
I'm not that fragile.

494
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:42,270
I mean when I separated from your dad,

495
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,400
I didn't ask for your opinion.

496
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,750
I just made you come with me.

497
00:21:46,070 --> 00:21:47,400
Why would you need my opinion?

498
00:21:47,750 --> 00:21:48,750
Isn't it obvious?

499
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:50,750
If you really had asked me,

500
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:51,480
then I'd blame you.

501
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:54,920
Our bond is strong, that's true.

502
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:57,830
But let's face it.

503
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:59,720
Your dad's a university professor.

504
00:22:00,590 --> 00:22:01,030
So what?

505
00:22:02,350 --> 00:22:04,160
He's now somewhat internet-famous.

506
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:06,400
Zhong Ning told me

507
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:07,830
he's currently earning

508
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:09,790
no less than I used to.

509
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:11,720
So?

510
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:16,270
His new wife is disgusting, yes.

511
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:19,240
But she owns a tutoring center.

512
00:22:19,790 --> 00:22:21,640
She must have
loads of educational resources.

513
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:23,070
If you stayed with your dad,

514
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,920
she could help you out.

515
00:22:25,070 --> 00:22:25,680
Stop.

516
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,110
Ms. Hu Manli,

517
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:28,590
no more such nonsense.

518
00:22:30,310 --> 00:22:31,270
Let's be honest here.

519
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,070
I'm just afraid if you stay with me,

520
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:34,110
I'll hold you back.

521
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:35,750
Wait.

522
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:36,550
Mom.

523
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:38,400
Why this sudden inferiority complex?

524
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:40,680
He's a professor, and you

525
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:41,830
went to vocational school.

526
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:42,960
So you're beneath him?

527
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,310
I just said...

528
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,590
Ms. Hu Manli.

529
00:22:48,070 --> 00:22:49,160
Open your eyes and look around.

530
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:50,680
Everything in this house

531
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:51,830
was bought with your money.

532
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,310
How are you inferior to him?

533
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,510
Don't you dare look down on yourself.

534
00:22:58,590 --> 00:22:59,640
Do you really think so?

535
00:23:02,550 --> 00:23:03,270
Ms. Hu Manli.

536
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:04,550
Be more confident.

537
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:06,310
Only incompetent people

538
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,160
need to flaunt money or resources

539
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,350
to prove their worth.

540
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:11,160
You'll always be the best to me.

541
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:12,830
That has never changed.

542
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:15,510
Thank you, Dingding.

543
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:16,380
Hmph.

544
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:19,270
What's with the "hmph"?

545
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,830
There's milk on your face.

546
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:23,920
Do your homework.

547
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:24,960
Don't stay up late.

548
00:23:25,580 --> 00:23:26,180
Oh.

549
00:24:46,350 --> 00:24:46,720
Hello?

550
00:24:47,510 --> 00:24:47,790
Hello?

551
00:24:48,110 --> 00:24:49,070
What about Ms. Zhou's deal?

552
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:51,590
Take it.

553
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,830
But we must clarify with Sun Jie.

554
00:24:55,590 --> 00:24:56,000
Why?

555
00:24:57,590 --> 00:24:58,720
We'll take this job

556
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,070
but we'll do it flawlessly,

557
00:25:01,070 --> 00:25:02,110
leaving no room for criticism.

558
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:05,960
Let everyone see my capability.

559
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:24,220
♫A dream I can't wake from♫

560
00:25:24,540 --> 00:25:26,820
♫Who sleepwalks through the haze♫

561
00:25:29,780 --> 00:25:31,700
♫Endless winds keep blowing on♫

562
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:34,740
♫Who truly understands♫

563
00:25:35,620 --> 00:25:38,940
♫Hearts divided by thick walls♫

564
00:25:39,380 --> 00:25:42,460
♫No shared pain we can recall♫

565
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:45,180
♫Our pains♫

566
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:48,060
♫Each bloom in separate ways♫

567
00:25:50,780 --> 00:25:55,260
♫Riding sunset clouds I'll fly♫

568
00:25:55,500 --> 00:25:58,820
♫Back to where our home once stood♫

569
00:25:59,100 --> 00:26:03,940
♫Skies forever clear and bright♫

570
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:08,900
♫Life's but a fleeting dream♫

571
00:26:09,340 --> 00:26:10,040
♫Yes it is♫

572
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:13,540
♫Love's the thread that holds us close♫

573
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:15,460
♫Keep loving♫

574
00:26:16,020 --> 00:26:19,540
♫Through the throes♫

575
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:31,880
I'll send your things tomorrow

576
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:32,830
by express to your school.

577
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:33,480
Remember to collect them.

578
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:43,590
What?

579
00:26:45,310 --> 00:26:46,880
She actually wants to
